  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen message is received to chat we do not move the chat item to the top of list of chats on `Chats`. It's randomly (could not identify pattern yet) sorted  and stands among list of the rest chat elements making it non user friendly as you need o scroll across whole list of chats to find out where new message received.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nChat items on `Chats` view sorted by the latest message received in chat. Thus, chat with latest message moves chat item to the top of the list\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nChat items on `Chats` view sorted randomly when mesage is received in chat.\r\n![ezgif-1-8f7b5d34534f](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/69148257-8e9da380-0adc-11ea-9d3d-64abe4e94127.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Join several public chats (or 1-1 chats) and read messages\r\n- Join different public chat for testing purposes (e.g. `#test1ordering`)\r\n- Navigate back to `Chats` view\r\n- By another contact send message to public chat  `#test1ordering`\r\n- Verify  `#test1ordering` moved to the top of the list of chats on `Chats` main view\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: develop` 0.14.0 (2019181102)`\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
